lass=title> Newbie Soloing - Help</span><hr size=1> Im just a young wizard of 7 Levels.  This is my first wizard, a High Elf on the Zebuxoruk server.  Anyway, I've started to notice that groups don't appreciate wizards much, and would rather not invite them.  Since I still need to kill to get exp, I want to learn to become a good, and efficient soloer.  Are there really any soloing techniques for my level? And where and what should I hunt?  I'm a newbie so, I must learn.  Any help will be greatly appreciated.  Thankyou. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/utaedirk.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Taedirk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/20/01 10:23:15 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=199.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Newbie Soloing - Help</span><hr size=1> Best soloing advice for you: Keep gate up, root, nuke, repeat.  If you try what I did at that age (root-rain-nuke), watch out for guards hiding in windmills (I swear to god, I will kill Forpar Fizfla one of these days.)  If it looks like you're in trouble, fade/shadowstep and gate.<br>
<br>
EDIT: If you don't follow Solusek Ro, you might want to think about restarting your character since you aren't too high yet.  It makes a few factions hate you a bit more, a few love you a bit more, and in the future it gives you access to some very good religious rings.  I still hate myself for being an Agnostic.  That advice also came from the person who told me AE spells were a very bad thing...he now plays a ranger.  Think there's a connection? <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :rolleyes --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/eyes.gif ALT=":rolleyes"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
